quran[35]{c,v,t}:
  26,70,"He asked his father and his people: \"What do you people worship"
  26,71,"We worship idols\" they said, and adore them with appropriate acts and rites and we are attached to them and unmoved in mind"
  26,72,"Do they hear you\", Ibrahim asked, \"when you praise them or supplicate"
  26,73,Or do they profit you or hurt
  26,74,"But\", they said, \"this is exactly the system of faith and worship our fathers adopted"
  26,75,"Do you see\", Ibrahim said, \"all those you adored and revered as objects of worship"
  26,76,And you and your fathers and your ancestors treated with respect and devotion
  26,77,"They are adversaries who might obtain their end and therefore enemies to me but not Allah, the Creator of the worlds, the visible and the invisible, past, present and those to come"
  26,78,The Creator- Who brought me into existence and it is He Who guides me to the truth and to the path of righteousness
  26,79,It is He Who provides me with victuals to eat and drinkables (to drink)
  26,80,"And when I fall sick, it is He Who restores me to health"
  26,81,And it is He Who determines the moment and the cause of my death and occasions my resurrection and restoration to life
  26,82,The Creator- Whom I hope will relent and quit me all His debt and will forgive me my wrongful actions when I have audience of Him in Day of Judgement
  26,83,"And to Him I express my thoughts in my invocatory prayer, thus: \"Confer on me O Allah, my Creator, wisdom to help me judge rightly in matters relating to physical and spiritual life and to impart to me soundness of judgement in the choice of means and ends, and unite me, O Allah, with the society of those in whose hearts reigns piety"
  26,84,"And furnish me O Allah, my Creator, with a civil tongue uttering the truth that guides into all truth and is believed among posterity"
  26,85,And if you destine me I will be one of those inheriting the Garden of the supreme bliss and blessedness
  26,86,"And extend O Allah my Creator, Your mercy and forgiveness lo my father who was lost in the maze of error\". (A prayer invoked by Ibrahim before he realized that his father was an enemy to Allah)"
  26,87,And do not confound me nor occasion me to fall from grace in Day of Judgement
  26,88,The Day when neither wealth nor progeny shall be of advantage
  26,89,"Except him who comes to the audience of Allah with his heart in its right place, heartened or filled with devotion"
  26,90,This is the Day when Paradise shall be brought quite near to these in whose hearts reigned piety
  26,91,And Hell is projected for those who were led by the nose to the maze of error and spent their days in vanity
  26,92,"They shall be asked: \"Where now are those you revered and adored with appropriate acts and rites"
  26,93,"The gods you revered and venerated besides Allah!\" Do they afford you help or can they even help themselves"
  26,94,There and then shall they -the infidels- be cast in Hell headlong one batch after another along with those who wasted their days in vanity
  26,95,And added to them shall be those who served Iblis AL-Shaytan (Satan) all into one gathering and in one place
  26,96,"And when all have been thronged -in Hell- and have exchanged angry altercation, they -the infidels- shall express their thoughts in words"
  26,97,"By Allah\", they say, \"we wandered indeed from the path of rectitude and were lost in the maze of error"
  26,98,"We have equalized you -false gods- with Allah, Creator of the worlds"
  26,99,"And they add:\" no one led us by the nose to the maze of error but the wicked who were given to sin and steeped in crime"
  26,100,"And now\", they will exclaim, \"no one can defend us nor shall we find intercessors who would interpose on our behalf"
  26,101,Nor do we find one who is joined to us in mutual benevolence and intimacy
  26,102,"If only\", they say, \"we could be given another chance of life below we would be among those who exercise low submissive obeisance to Allah and entertain the profound reverence dutiful to Him"
  26,103,This is indeed emblematic of Allah's Omnipotence and Authority but most of them deny Allah Who brought them into existence
  26,104,"Allah, your Creator, is indeed AL-Aziz and AL-Rahim"